 As a way of giving back to the community Emnotweni Casino and Entertainment donated funds for stairs, wheelchair ramps and rails at KaMagugu Inclusive School. The school that enrols pupils with mild to moderate learning barriers, as well as learners in high need of support.
Some of the learners in the school use wheelchairs and the ramps and rails will make easier for them to get around. ALSO READ:KaMagugu Inclusive School, giving special-needs children the best start in life Last week Friday the team from Emnotweni officially handed over their contribution to the principal, Eric Ndashe.
Andries Scholtz, the deputy principal, said that the school appreciates the contribution. “We are satisfied and we want to thank Emnotweni Casino and Entertainment for what they for the learners,” said Scholtz.